casebody.data:
Second Department,

September, 1945.

(September 26, 1945.) The People of the State of New York ex rel. Louis Silvers, Relator, against Warden of the City Prison, 149 Ashland Place, Borough of Brooklyn, City of New York, Respondent.

Return on writ of habeas corpus. Bail reduced to $25,000, writ dismissed and the relator remanded to custody. Present — Close, P. J., Carswell, Adel, Lewis and Aldrich, JJ.
